SUMMARY:Benefit Show for the Permanent People’s Tribunal on Missing Indi
 genous Children and Unmarked Graves
LOCATION:4848 St-Laurent (métro Laurier)
DESCRIPTION:2026-03-31 18:30:00\n\n4848 St-Laurent (métro Laurier)\n\nhtt
 ps://www.openstreetmap.org/node/2084779406\n\nThe Native Women’s Shelter
  is thrilled to announce this important event on March 31st. Join us for a
  benefit concert featuring Jeremy Dutcher and Ribbon Skirt!!\nThe proceeds
  will go towards to upcoming Permanent People’s Tribunal on Missing Indi
 genous Children and Unmarked Graves\, May 25-29\, 2026. Huge thanks to our
  partners\, the David Suzuki Foundation\, daphne art centre\, POP Montreal
 \, and the Survivors Secretariat. More details will come soon! Please shar
 e!!
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.openstreetmap.org/node/2084779406
END:VEVENT
